title: The Marriage Pact
description: We're Chams and Deen. And together we made a marriage pact when we were 17. Seemed safe at the time, I mean what were the odds we’d still be single at age 30? Well ten years later those odds are looking pretty bleak. So we decided to take action before it’s too late. Together we’re going to explore our dating history over the last ten years and figure out where we’ve gone wrong. Retell old love stories, recount fleeting romances, maybe even consult some experts, you know, get professional help. Because we really don’t want to marry each other. I mean we like each other fine but it’s more of a structural issue. And if you can’t read between the lines, we both like boys. Hopefully by sharing our journey with the world we’ll help some other people out or if not, at the very least we’ll do our best to be entertaining and we’ll get to hear the sound of our own voices.

title: Processing The Process Podcast
description: In 2020, I decided to cut the crap and take care of myself and go to therapy to process my shiiiiiiet. Shortly after, this podcast was born! Here, we talk about anxiety, self-love, self-care, inner child healing, enjoying the f*ck of your food and *actual* existence, as well as placing mental health as a priority. Let me be your mental health and self-love bestie!!! I GOT U bby!!!!!! In this podcast, we explore the lessons learned and how we can process every process we face in the most tender, but firm ways. Sometimes self-love and self-care are scary, absolutely isolating, and messy--nothing like face masks or bubble baths. Be tender with yourself, man! It can feel heavy! But I encourage you. Open yourself up to the possibility that life can feel and be better, even on the most darkest days. You got this. Keep mf goin!!! I love you endlessly!!! :-)

title: Creatively Relating with Vyana Novus
description:
Multimedia artist & parent Vyana Novus explores relational wellness through the lens of creativity. They merge their experiences of integrating complex trauma and chronic illness with a mindful, multidimensional mindset focused on creative expression. 
|
Some topics you'll hear discussed on the show include personal responsibility, creatively exploring presence, sexual liberation, trauma recovery, relating after abuse, conscious parenting, cultivating sustainable joy, being in relationship with ourselves, intergenerational trauma, deep time, and more.
|
For context, Vyana comes to the show with lived trauma experienced in the realms of (CW) early childhood incestuous rape, physical abuse, emotional & psychological abuse, drug addiction, and eating disorders.
|
Their professional background is diverse and expansive including creative directing, writing, branding, styling, illustration, allergen-free baking, massage therapy, teaching energy medicine, yoga, meditation, and adult & children's art classes.
As a student of Radical Relating, Vyana's perspective is greatly informed by relating through difference in a grounded, skillful way.
|
|
|
Creatively Relating is color-coded.
Orange Circle: episodes with a guest
Grey/Green Circle: episodes with only Vyana
|
Both circles were painted with earth pigment watercolor paint harvested and made by Vyana.
|
Follow Vyana on Instagram @vyana.novus
Call into the show at 1-833-2RELATE // 1-833-273-5283 or write in at creativelyrelating@gmail.com

description: The Please Hustle Responsibly Podcast is the brainchild of our Support Staff team members Kristina Magro, Kristina Veltri, and Matt Kohl. Support Staff’s goals are to break down the stigmas surrounding mental health, give employers tools to better support their employees, and give hourly employees tools to better advocate for their well-being. How are we doing that? Through programs like this podcast! Inspired by the hospitality industry and our wants and needs during this COVID-19 crisis, Magro sums it up the goal of this podcast best by stating, “we decided that instead of being better advocates for everyone else we are going to be better advocates for ourselves and for the hospitality industry as a whole.” Join us on our podcasting adventure as we talk with professionals about everything from how to navigate your health insurance to dealing with HR and and the unemployment office.

title: Language 180
description:
Integrating the twin Great Commission tasks of language learning and gospel communication, Language 180 gets to the heart of gospel fluency across cultures. 

Language 180 is a reorientation, a complete pivot in perspective: We're reminded that language learning is something we don’t have to do before we share the gospel, rather something we get to do while we share the gospel.

Language 180 is a reminder to persevere when we're tempted to plateau. Language 180 also refers to the minutes we spend every day in ongoing learning toward a sustained lifestyle of evangelism and discipleship in the language. In other words, through Language 180 we practice learning the language to communicate the gospel 3 hours per day, 60 minutes in each of three activities - personal preparation (1st hour), deliberate practice (2nd hour), and fluent proclamation (3rd hour) - for a total of 180 minutes each day. Want to learn more? Start with the first episode, "What is Language 180?"

In the Language 180 podcast, we explore core concepts that sync with articles and resources found on the language180.com website where we learn to: 1) Understand the basics of gospel fluency across cultures 2) Align our perspective with God’s perspective on gospel fluency 3) Evangelize our lost neighbors as we learn their language 4) Comprehend and tell simple familiar gospel stories in our new language 5) Engage our neighbors through the limitless radius of the gospel in all life encounters 6) Learn to listen and respond as an integral part of the fluency needed to reach neighbors with the gospel 7) Know what it means to intelligently learn a language 8) Invest in life-long language learning 9) Practice Language 180 for fruitful ongoing learning and in-language ministry 10) Converse the gospel in our new language 11) Share our testimony; pray for our neighbors, and 12) Identify as Kingdom pilgrims, with an unwavering assurance in our destination and an insatiable desire to invite others to join us from the “nations of every language” (Zechariah 8:23).

title: 啊！ 是猫咪呀！
description:
【啊！是猫咪呀】是一档致力于探索人性和人物心理学的播客。

「猫咪」一词来源于美国电影编剧布莱克·斯奈德创造的编剧法则：被他称之为「救猫咪」的场面，是主人公做了某件事——比如救了一只猫咪——从而让观众认可、喜欢上他的决定性时刻。

我们剖析影视作品里的人物故事、观察普通人的生活、研究群体的心理现象，也会深挖自己的内心，旨在找出隐藏在形形色色故事里的「猫咪」——那些反映人性中真实、复杂、幽微的元素。

好奇心与同理心泛滥的我们，欣赏复杂而深邃的人性刻画，抵抗非黑即白的二元思维，关心个人成长，期待人与万物间持续发展出奇妙的联结。

title: Conversations about Consultation
description: Welcome to our podcast, Conversations about Consultation. This is a series of digital audio files, made with a wide range of guests who have been generous enough to share their thinking on the topic of consultation in education. Our aim is to provide thought-provoking and engaging content that you can access at times and in places convenient to you, growing out of our shared interest in consultation. Emma teaches a module on the M4 doctoral training in educational psychology that includes consultation, and Jessica, Emily and Zahra are all doctoral students currently on placement in local authority settings making use of consultation in their work. Consultation has any number of different definitions and models. Given our training and background, we are especially interested in consultation as it is used in schools and community settings. We see consultation as a particular type of professional helping relationship, one that holds central the idea that it is the relationship between the consultant and those with whom they work that makes the difference. However, one aim of Conversations about Consultation is to speak with guests who perhaps use different lenses, modalities and approaches and who offer something unique and distinctive that can complement or contrast with our own. It may be a current trainee on a different programme whose research interests include consultation, or an early career practitioner reflecting on consultative working in schools. We speak with experienced practitioners from other disciplines who bring their expertise in working with children young people and their families; as well as psychologists who have been working in the field of consultation research and practice for many years. We hope you will find a conversation to listen to that engages your interest, offers a different perspective or even just provokes a new question or idea that leads to further conversations of your own. You can follow us on twitter to join in the conversation at @TheCACpodcast

title: Pari Suhteesta
description:
Pari Suhteesta on Aleksin ja Sandran sukellus parisuhteeseen. Se on sielukas katselmus henkisestä matkasta, jota parisuhde peilaa.  Kuinka miehen ja naisen suhde voi toimia? Kuinka molemmat osapuolet voivat kukoistaa? Kuinka "me" näyttäytyy yksilötasolla ja kuinka "minä" käyttäytyy yhteisellä tasolla? Puhumme rehellisesti tantrisesta seksuaalisuudesta, tunteista ja kasvustamme tässä suhteessa.

Aleksi on kouluttautunut kundaliinijoogaohjaaja. Lisäksi Aleksin henkisiin harjoitteisiin kuuluvat hengitys- ja kehonpainoharjoitteet, laulu, kitaransoitto, leikkimielisyys, vapaa ekstaattinen tanssi sekä suuri rakkaus ja kunnioitus kylmäaltistusta kohtaan. Aleksilla on valtava halu tuoda henkistä syvyyttä länsimaiselle keholle ja mielelle helpommin lähestyttävässä muodossa. Hän on vahva kehorakkauden puolestapuhuja. 

Sandra opiskeli viisi vuotta psykologiaa yliopistossa, kunnes koki itsessään sen, että tie sisäiseen voimaan ja kukoistukseen löytyy länsimaista psykologiaa laajemman kehollisen varjotyöskentelyn, seksuaalisuuden ja sielullisuuden kautta. Niinpä Sandra jätti yliopisto-opinnot kesken ja opiskelee nyt Fertility Awareness- ja Sexual Health Educator :iksi etänä Yhdysvalloista. Sandra tutkii elämää tantran kautta, jossa seksuaalienergia nähdään pyhänä elämänenergiana ja joka tukee kokijaansa löytämään viisauden omasta kehostaan.

Tervetuloa podcastimme pariin!
-Sandra & Aleksi

* Muista seurata meitä myös instagramissa: @pari__suhteesta *

Having improved self-worth is the path for a happier life full of love and purpose.  Learn why self-worth is so essential to our mental health.  Episodes will include evidence-based strategies to help transform your self-worth and candid conversations with inspiring humans who get raw and real as they share their personal stories of perseverance, empowerment, mental health struggles, business success and relationships.  Kimberly Mueller, a registered psychologist, offers relatable content connecting science with practical self-help tools and Lara Smith, founder and CEO of a luxury apparel company shares her story of escaping an abusive relationship and how she was able to heal and personally and professionally thrive afterwards.

title: Kids are PEOPLE too!
description: Kids are PEOPLE Too is a parenting podcast where the host, Celita Williams, approaches various topics from the perspective of helping parents to examine and possibly reshape their parenting philosophies and manage expectations of their children. The conversations are based on scientifically proven timelines for child psychological and cognitive development. This is not a traditional parenting podcast. We do talk about how to modify the behavior of our children to achieve desired outcomes, but we also focus on how to look within to find ways that we, as parents, may be contributing to our own parenting challenges. Most importantly, we focus on how to revamp our approach and overcome our parenting struggles.

title: High Frequency Females
description: High Frequency Females is a space in time for women who are trying to live a life of a higher vibration. A space where women can be unapologetic for being their true and authentic selves and speak their truth with conviction, free of judgement and pressure. I'll be talking to incredible women who are experts in their fields, such as psychologists, poets, personal trainers even reiki healers, psychics and yoga teachers. Women who can guide us on our life's journey. I'll also be having conversations with women who have lived real and emotional experiences. Experiences we need to humanise and bring light to. Areas and problems in society which aren’t always discussed publicly whether it's from shame or embarrassment. I want to create safe space for women to take their power back. We all have so much to learn, we need to learn to support each other and raise our vibrations as a collective, because we're all living this human experience. Living a life at a higher frequency is a place I want all women to live, and to have the strength to empower ourselves to start living the life we want and the life which we deserve. Welcome to the High Frequency Females Podcast. Xxxx

Justyne & Tori

title: SmartLoving Conversations
description:
A place to discuss all things Catholic marriage!  Married life is messy!
Hosted by Francine Pirola and Laura Cain, our live conversations seek to go deeper into the mystery - and the messy reality - of living Catholic marriage.
With our guests, we explore love, marriage, family and living our Catholic faith.
We've set our sights on heaven but our real and honest conversations keep our feet on the ground. We've had our triumphs and struggles and so have our guests.
For smarter or dumber, for happy or grumpy, in abundance and scarcity - we're ready to talk!

Each week they'll dive into random a** topics like dating in SF, sex, therapy, the ugly side of Silicon Valley, Burning Man, blind wine tasting, crypto, neighborhood gems, and more all on MOMS BEING MOMS.

title: Remarkably Us
description: In this podcast we’re stripping the bullshit and getting down to the unfiltered parts of life through raw, authentic, and often difficult conversations. We’re talking about resilience, about picking yourself up from some extreme lows and rising stronger. Through my personal journey of self discovery, and sobriety, I’ve learned and continue to learn what it takes to get up and stay up. We’re sharing stories and all of the tools collected in maintaining a consistent environment for self growth, love and discovery. We’ll hear from others who are breaking barriers and climbing incredibly tough mountains. Connection matters, stories matter and without that we are nothing. So, get ready to get inspired and motivated, to laugh and to cry. But most importantly, to love a little.

title: CFC House of Harvest Ministries

​CFC House of Harvest Ministries, in Midrand, South Africa is run by us, Senior Pastors, Zwelibanzi and Susan Mazabane. Both of us were ordained by founders of CFC International, Drs Theo and Beverly Worlmarans in 2006.

title: Conscious Rebellion with Samantha Sacchi
description:
It often feels humanity has gone a bit astray. I get it. What are we doing here? I’m Samantha Sacchi from The Self Club. I always knew life was this temporary experience- a soul in a borrowed physical body, I wasn’t sure why so many people spent so much time on things that don’t matter at all. I get it now, they just didn’t know. They were all still asleep. 

I’m deep and have been writing, philosophizing, and trying to understand life since I’m 10. I moved 18 times across 4 continents by the age of 28, which also made me question pretty much everything. My background is in International Economics and Business, Leadership Development and Emotional Intelligence. I've studied from neuro-linguistic programming​, to Reiki and Akashic records, to natural and holistic nutrition to look at life from a truly holistic perspective​. 

This podcast is a conscious rebellion to shift from a ​fear-based system that keeps us small and doubtful to a way of living based on truth, trust and love as we access our own innate wisdom. A new paradigm that starts with radical self-awareness, a new educational system and a conscious way of being human - combining ancient wisdom with modern knowledge. I'll be hosting and bringing you conversations with conscious souls that are part of this shift. 

This new paradigm starts with you.

title: Mentor Podcast

John Roy is a purple belt in Brazilian Jiu Jitsu, a firefighter, a husband and father. With their combined experience, both hosts seek out interesting people to interview for each episode that can serve as "mentors" for others. Guests include elite athletes, people who work honorable jobs (I.e. military, doctor, etc.), or anyone who has an interesting story to tell that may help someone build character or find inspiration in their own life.

The show is hosted by Dr. Bonnie Bonita,  Author, Advocate, Motivational Speaker & Successful Entrepreneur.

title: The Terez Leclerc podcast
description: My time in Burma started difficult, yet it became one of the most profound experiences I've had to date. I found myself alone in a closed country, with nothing familiar around me. Because of the extreme circumstances, Jesus became more real to me than ever before, and because there was no one else to rely on, I began to hear His voice loud and so clear. Thus we spent our time in conversation. This is a story that's never fully been told, its about how when everything was stripped away and I had nothing left but Jesus to hold on to, how He became more real to me than ever. It was my adventure with Holy Spirit. Raw, real yet true. I came back with new eyes, and a completely fresh perspective. All that mattered was Him. it was a time of growth and renewal. And the ministry there was something else. Everything that happened had a powerful effect on me, and one that would last a life time.

title: Naturalies
description:
Naturalies.
 
My name is Samantha-Jo, I am the host for this amazing podcast that I am hoping save souls. My reasoning for starting this podcast came about after I gave my life to Christ on July 11, 2021. I started finding myself constantly want to talk about my struggles (HOT: humble, open & transparent), the things that have given me strength, the things God has done for me & most importantly the things I know that God has for me. I know you're thinking "oh here we go with some religious podcast" but I'm asking that you look deeper than that. I am a Christian & yes I pray this podcast changes lives in ways beyond my belief but if its not enough to convince you to stay I will also mention the other things I am that God has allowed me to be. I am a single Mother of 4, YES FOUR amazing boys who at the end of this year will be 12, 6, 4 & 2. I am a business owner (if you have instagram JosCraftShack & Sheis.waisted).  I am also a nurse, I have been for almost 4 years now. So again if religion isnt enough to convince you to stay then stick around for the other things I have to offer.

Why Naturalies?
I recently (1 year ago) left a very toxic relationship after 8 years & literally started completely over in the middle of the pandemic with all 4 children. I literally built my own kitchen table, tv stand, coffee table, my bed & childrens bed & started over knowing only what I thought I knew. Black women have been placed in boxes all of our lives. "Starting over is harder than you think so you should probably stay" "You cant do it without this person or that person", "You have to act this way, its not lady like to do it that way", "You cant jump out on faith because nobody in our family has done that", "You cant be better than what you come from", "your idea isnt good enough to take you there" ALL LIES, LIES, AND MORE LIES THAT PEOPLE HAVE PLACED ON BLACK WOMEN & LADIES YOU DO NOT HAVE TO AGREE TO MEET ANY STANDARD YOU, YOURSELF, DID NOT SET! This is my safe haven for black women, no matter what you look like, your body size, your bank account or profession, single mom, married mom, in a bad situation, left a bad situation LISTEN I do not care. Come, let your hair down, act the way you want to act even if it doesn't make sense to anyone else, cry a little, heal a lot & know that this is a sisterhood.

Im so ready for this journey. I love you ladies.

How to gain emotional freedom AND stay a Teacher

How to take back your brain from the pressures of the world, so that you can focus on what you love to do, Teach!

THE BONUS: Along the way you learn how to work with any colleague along with ANY student that comes into your life.

title: JOONAS - Jongeren en Ouders Ondersteunen NA Scheiding
description:
“Wat is het belang van het kind? Wat is de rol van het parket bij een scheiding? Wat is levend verlies bij scheiding? Wat vertellen kinderen en jongeren aan AWEL over de scheiding van hun ouders? Maar ook .. wat zijn risico en beschermende factoren voor kinderen en jongeren? Wanneer en hoe zet je best bemiddeling in? Wat is ouderverstoting en hoe herken je het?" Dat èn zoveel meer… 
In JOONAS, de podcast waarmee we Jongeren en Ouders willen Ondersteunen NA Scheiding draait elke aflevering om één centrale vraag. Rond die centrale vraag gaan wij open, maar kritisch in gesprek met een deskundige uit hulpverlening en/of justitiële wereld èn getuigen ervaringsdeskundigen via geluidsfragmenten over hun ervaringen. 
JOONAS is een initiatief van psycholoog en psychotherapeut Vanessa Maes en familiaal bemiddelaar - advocaat Sophie Vanhemmens.
Hun doel? dat zit in de naam… jongeren en ouders ondersteunen na een scheiding… door erkenning en herkenning te bieden in de vele verhalen uit de 2 werelden: die van hulpverlening en die van justitie. 
Wil je ook getuigen? Wil je ons helpen bij het maken van deze podcast? Tips? Reacties? Vragen?
Meer weten of ons volgen? 
Facebookpagina: https://www.facebook.com/joonasdepodcast
Instagrampagina: https://instagram.com/joonas_depodcast
Wil je ons steunen? 
Dan mag dit integraal gaan naar AWEL. Voor onze kinderen en jongeren. Dit mag op het rekeningnummer: BE63 0689 3013 1108. Alvast bedankt!

title: Ενσυναίσθηση - Σε μια κοινωνία που δεν ξέρει να πενθεί
description:
Το πόνημα αυτό δεν είναι ένα κλασικό βιβλίο που θα σε κτυπήσει φιλικά στον ώμο και θα σου πει ότι «όλα γίνονται για κάποιο λόγο», «ο Θεός παίρνει τους καλούς», «τουλάχιστον τον έζησες και τον είχες κοντά σου για αρκετά χρόνια» και άλλα τέτοια. Δεν θα σου πει ότι αυτό που περνάς θα γίνει σύντομα πιο ελαφρύ ή θα το ξεπεράσεις. Ούτε θα προσπαθήσει να σε κάνει να νικήσεις το πένθος σου λες και είναι κάποια αρρώστια. Δεν θα επιχειρήσει να ανάγει ένα τραγικό γεγονός σε κάτι ανώτερο και να το εξηγήσει μεταφυσικά ή από θρησκευτική σκοπιά. Θα σε στηρίξει στο να ζήσεις με το πένθος σου, να το καταλάβεις, να συμφιλιωθείς με αυτό και να περπατήσετε μαζί στο νέο άδικο μονοπάτι που σε έβαλε η ζωή. Μια ζωή που δεν έχει λογική και όπου το σύμπαν δεν ανταμείβει τους καλούς, ούτε τους προσέχει, ούτε τους χρωστάει τίποτα. 
Στις 27 Δεκέμβρη του 2020, έχασα τον πιο σημαντικό άνθρωπο της μέχρι τότε ζωής μου αλλά και της μετέπειτα. Κατέρρευσαν τα πάντα και ένα πανέμορφο εσωτερικά κορίτσι 36 ετών μόνο, έκλεισε τα μάτια και δεν τα ξανάνοιξε . . .

The Heart Story Podcast is a collection of wisdom to take you to deeper Love. Each podcast guest is chosen to bring a deeper sense of awareness and connection in your relationship with yourself and how that reflects outwardly to all relationships. The Heart Story was created for Women who are in the midst of a transition period in their relationships. Clearing the space that has been occupied by the past and allow yourself to receive love in the fullest. This is for conscious women who are changing the roles, from single to engaged, or engaged to married. This program is a collaboration of holistic healing contributors and will gently lead the way into the peaceful transformation. Some of the Key components of this course are listed below - During life, you will experience deep change within yourself as you will be moving into unknown territory. With each role change you will have different needs and desires. The three transition phases this program will help you navigate are: From Single Seeker to Lover Commitment & Wife Satisfaction You were a different person many times in your life as you have evolved through the experiences and relationships. When you notice a thought pattern or behavior coming up and can see this is repetitive or not serving your relationship, this would be the space to cultivate the change within yourself. Loving Relationships come with many frustrations as you very well know. Navigating these space requires knowledge, wisdom, practice and skill. With the program and the book club, we hold the space for you to work through what comes up as you transition into the Queen. You will experience your deep desires and begin to attract them to you, similar to Bees & Honey The investment for a self development program is one that will pay you dividends of increased peace for the rest of your life. You will learn the art of containment and be able to transmute your fear, anger or grief into a space of love to share with your partner. This will help ensure that your needs will be met in the loving space of a lifetime love. www.theheartstory.com

title: The Memorial of a Shy Black Girl
description: Hey y'all! My name is DaAujana and welcome to my spoken word diary. Inspiration for this diary was drawn from a multitude of sources, but the main one being high school and my first semester of college. I've always been shy and introverted and isn't a bad thing by any means, but it has caused me to feel an overwhelming amount emotions that have been not so good along the way. The biggest thing I've had to cope with is being alone and not feeling so confident sometimes - and because of that, it has caused me in the past and in the present to withstand what feels to be an uphill battle. Thus, I want to share my stories with all of you because we are going through our own ups and downs. We are all impacted by the actions of our world and instead of remaining shy and silent, I want to use my voice to empower others through sharing my own stories(both serious and ridiculous ones) and truly journey through the process of stepping out of ones embarrassment, shyness, shame, etc and truly being who you are. This journey is also like a mini journal for me to spill out and say all of the things that I have wanted to express for so long, but hadn't because I was too afraid to- I can only hope that through my courage and my words that it will encourage you all to feel empowered to truly be unapologetically yourself and slowly show people the real you and step into your true prime.⚡️

title: Be Ready
description:
Questions, Concerns, Comments? 
Please email me at jmmrunningtherace@gmail.com.
_____________________________________________________________________________________________ 
    Dear Listener, 
Are you ready? There are many things in life to prepare for: college, gameday, a career, marriage, having a family, owning a home, retirement. Preparing for these endeavors is part of life’s journey; personally, I have worked to prepare myself for many of them. But even more, I am in the process of preparing myself for an even greater event than getting married or owning my own home, as great as these things are. I am preparing to meet the King who is coming back someday for His people. 

Dear Listener, my name is Josiah Moldenhauer, and the purpose of this podcast is to help you prepare as well, prepare to meet this King of the Ages who is coming soon for those who believe in Him and follow Him. Who is this King? He is also known as the King of Glory. He is the Chosen One who came to redeem us back to God from our sin and shame that we may know Him as Father and save us from Hell that we might know Heaven as home. 

Jesus Himself tells us at the end of the book of Revelation: “Behold, I am coming soon! My reward is with me, and I will give to everyone according to what he has done. I am the Alpha and the Omega, the First and the Last, the Beginning and the End. Blessed are those who wash their robes, that they may have the right to the tree of life and may go through the gates into the city. Outside are the dogs, those who practice magic arts, the sexually immoral, the murderers, the idolaters and everyone who loves and practices falsehood. ‘I, Jesus, have sent my angel to give you this testimony for the churches. I am the Root and Offspring of David, and the bright Morning Star.’” (Revelation 22:12-16, NIV 1984). 

Dear Listening Friend, have you washed your sin-stained robes in the blood of the Lamb? I’m so glad I have! He has forgiven and cleansed me of my sins. If you have never met the Savior, He stands at the door of your heart and knocks. Open the door to Him while there is still time; you do not want to be left outside in the dark. Hell is as terrible and real as Heaven is glorious. Jesus said, “The thief comes only to steal and kill and destroy. I came that they may have life and have it abundantly (John 10:10, ESV). Jesus offers true spiritual life with God now and for eternity. He is the only one who gives living water that quenches our thirsty souls. 

 “The Spirit [of God] and the bride say, “Come!” And let him who hears say, “Come!” Whoever is thirsty, let him come; and whoever wishes, let him take the free gift of the water of life (Rev. 22:17, NIV). 

Dear friend, join me on a journey of knowing and following this Jesus together as we prepare for His glorious coming! As we learn to believe in Him, to love Him with our lives, and to long for His return. Our King is coming back soon! He told us, “Therefore keep watch, because you do not know on what day your Lord will come” (Matt. 24:42, NIV).

Grace and Peace to you in Jesus Christ the Lord.

description:
Christian... A title synonymous with son's of God. But many that carry the title more than lack in their abilities to reflect the attributes given of God. Unfortunately Christianity as a whole has failed to be evidence of the Glory of God among men, but this was the first thing that Christ did in all His works. So how could we possibly declare the deity of the word made flesh and fail to reflect all that he made possible in us? 

   From one end of God's word to the other, we were warned of the short comings that would befall much of the body of Christ. This is the venue designed to give revelation of the elements that have effectually hindered us from walking as Son's of the most high. The question is what will you do once you know the truth? 
   In the call of a modern day Apostle it is imperative that my actions and intent clearly manifest honor of all that God is. Moreover I declare nothing of myself except that I must be subject to the directives of His Holy Spirit.  For even as in times past, a true Apostle must glorify God in all of his endeavors. The mandate to point the hearts of man back to Father God is the sole purpose of my ministry efforts. A messenger need not prove a thing, God will reveal Himself. That is to all who dare to truly seek Him.
   Change isn't a hard thing at all. the problem is accepting that there is a need for change. If you can muster the revelation of your own hidden motives, I can guarantee that the teachings to be found here will be a great assistance in finding the launch pad for change in your own life.

title: Bill Crockett: Touch of the Master's Hand
description:
The "Touch of the Master's Hand" is a Christian poem written in 1921 by Myra Brooks Welch. It is depicted in the painting by Ken Brooks used in our Podcast cover art. It tells of an old, battered violin that is about to be sold as the last item in an auction. The highest bid was $3. When suddenly a man in the back of the auction hall walked to the front of the building, took the violin from the auctioneer, wiped off the dust, tuned it and began to play. As he played, the patrons could hardly believe that such a melody could come from such a battered instrument. The violinist finished playing, handed the instrument back to the auctioneer, and walked back to his seat. Amazed and astonished the auctioneer softly said, "Now how much am I bid for this violin?" Instead of $3, the violin was sold for $3,000. The crowd asked, "What was it that suddenly brought value to such a battered instrument?" The auctioneer replied, "It was the touch of the master's hand!" The poem goes on to draw the analogy between the violin and a person whose life has been battered and torn by sin. Just as the master violinist brought value to the old violin, Jesus, our Creator, the Master of the universe and lover of our soul, will make our lives valuable, no matter how battered we may be!

Bill Crockett has a masters degree in Biblical Exposition and has served as an evangelist, pastor, counsellor and Bible Conference speaker across the US and in many countries. Bill also worked in corporate sales and sales management for almost 25 years. Having experienced divorce, the loss of a job, death of an immediate family member and depression to the point of suicide, he understands the ups and downs of life. At one point feeling as if God did not love or care about him, he discovered the true meaning of a personal walk with God and found renewed purpose and value as God touched his life once again!

"Touch of the Master's Hand" is a podcast sharing practical truths from the Bible that will help us realize our value and live productive and fulfilled lives as we are touched by the truth of God's Word.

Enlighten Me, B!#©h, hosted by the dynamic and effervescent Wrenn Woods, is a podcast about connection, communication, and comprehension. It’s intellectual. It’s blunt. It’s raw. It’s real. And, of course, it’s spicy AF. 

Unafraid to tell you like it is, Wrenn does not hold back. She shares stories and insights based on the trials and tribulations of her own life experiences as well as those of her guests. Motivated by a curious mind, Wrenn explores relationships, sex, adventure, addiction, psychological influences, emotions, the esoteric, and the meaning of life. With a sunny disposition, Wrenn uses humor, empathy, and intuitive awareness to help you find the light in the darkness of this world. You want to know how to find stability when there is an absolute train wreck of a shit storm happening around you? This is the podcast for you, sweetie. Life at any age is mayhem. Ground yourself in the chaos and learn to appreciate your own bedlam. Wrenn is here to make sure you don’t spiral and start living your best life. Stop trippin’ over the bullshit already. It’s going to give you wrinkles. Repeat after me: I am stable. I am able. I am wealthy. I am healthy. Working on yourself is sexy. Come into your power already, bitch. We’re evolving.

title: The Principle Podcast
description:
How do we influence others for good?

I am on a mission to inspire as many people as I can to learn principles of influence so that they can influence those they love, and work with, for good.

Principles govern the consequences of our choices. So let's figure out what they are - especially when it comes to very important things like our relationships. We have two choices when we encounter a principle: 1) align with it; or, 2) ignore it to our peril. Take the principle of gravity: we can align with it– build a hydroelectric dam, start a skydiving company, build a ski resort, etc.–or we can ignore it to our peril and fall off a cliff. Gravity doesn’t change. Our respect and alignment (or not) with the principle is the only thing that changes. Principles govern relationships, too. They, like gravity, are ancient and timeless. And we have the same choice: align or ignore. Learn how principles govern the consequences of all of our choices.

-EksAyn Anderson xfactoredge.com

Yet months and years have gone by and we are still wondering  what’s next; marriage, careers, businesses, toilet paper shortage, spiked gas prices? With COVID-19 making its debut not to long after walking the virtual graduation stage, we are taking the opportunity to really sit, be still and think;  what the heck are we supposed to be doing right now? What do  we want to come from our lives because what we were expecting has not revealed itself as promised? We were told by our elders to do what you love and you’ll never work a day in your life. And chile, we do not want to work!

FANG stands for “First American-Nigerian Generation” and the creators are Mukrimat & Rebecca.

Topics on Mondays, which I call Manaʻo Monday share Hawaiian culture lessons I learned from my kupuna (elder), Kumu (teacher), and kula (school) in Hawaii. On Fridays, which are called Aloha Fridays I highlight formal Hawaii residents by talkingstory with them about their relocation journey and experiences.  

This podcast intends to share the voices and stories of native Hawaiians, aka KĀNAKA MAOLI, and the Hawaiians of heart, that relocated away from our homeland of Hawaii.  My goal is to share these stories so we can all learn about others and understand the different situations.  Because the more we know the more we grow.

title: Cultivated Space: DU Native Histories
description: Hello Everyone! I am Reshawn Edison, your host for this series. Cultivated Space reflects my Capstone project as an undergraduate student at the University of Denver Anthropology Department. I explore the reckoning between Indigenous identity In higher education by those who have a relationship with the university. As a predominantly white institution, the University of Denver has upheld an unjust climate within its structure and culture. DU has maintained a hostile academic environment that Native American scholars and their allies constantly struggle with. I highlight these forms of navigation at a collective level. Join me as we validate Indigenous Identity because our relations narrative is critical to making actual change. This project is dedicated to the University of Denver Indigenous community, our allies, and extended relatives. To all my Indigenous peers across Turtle Island in higher education: Our voice, experiences, and stories matter.

Join us as we share our heart, principles from God's Word, and tools and ideas to help you build a stronger marriage. We'll laugh together; maybe shed a few tears together, but most importantly, challenge and encourage you to trust that God can do a work in your marriage as he did in ours. Join Sarah as she fearlessly dives into the messy realm of adulthood, regaling you with stories that will make you nod in agreement, laugh out loud, and maybe even shed a tear or two. From navigating the treacherous waters of self-discovery to exploring the depths of the human spirit, Sarah fearlessly tackles topics that will leave you feeling inspired and empowered.

Each episode is a treasure trove of wisdom and insight, delivered with Sarah's signature charm and infectious enthusiasm. Whether you're seeking advice on how to adult like a boss or craving a deeper understanding of yourself and the world around you, Aspiring Adult has you covered.

So, fasten your seatbelts and prepare for a podcasting adventure like no other. Tune in as Sarah Smiles serves up a piping hot plate of life lessons, spirituality, and emotional intelligence. Get ready to laugh, learn, and grow with Aspiring Adult.

Brittany Eldridge is an author, owner of Rise Above Radio, and passionate for mental health. She has written articles for the Rochester Voice, Better Because Project, NoStigmas, Made of Million Foundation and the Scars of Survival magazine. Her self-published books can be found at Riverrun bookstore in downtown Portsmouth, NH and also on Audible, Kindle, Barne's & Noble online, lulu.com and many others. You can also find Brittany's book Chasing Fireflies in the Rochester, Durham, Dover, Portsmouth and Manchester public library including the NH State Public Library. title: Tikva Talks
description:
In an effort to provide resources for those facing infertility and to educate the broader community, Yesh Tikva launched “Tikva Talks,” a set of conversations with field experts about issues surrounding infertility and reproductive health.

Traditionally, reproductive health is not a subject publicly discussed in the Jewish community. Tikva Talks allows Yesh Tikva to openly discuss the topic, while also raising awareness and sensitivity.

Some of the topics we’ve covered include:

Men and infertility
Impact of infertility on sexual intimacy
Maintaining relationships 
The challenges of Mikvah (ritual bath)
If you would like us to cover a topic not yet discussed in previous Tikva Talks please contact us!

title: The Chosen Families Project
description:
Often met with unfortunate circumstances, or even mutual disinterest, old photographs often get separated from those who once knew them. These photos can travel further from their place of origin, and become altogether removed from their identities. The Chosen Families Project uses the power of genealogy to understand their origins, tell their stories, and hopefully return them to their loved ones. I want to be able to welcome them into a family they can call home once more–as part of my chosen family.I want to be able to welcome them into a family they can call home once more–as part of my chosen family. I also want to initiate conversations about genealogy, what can be changed in the traditional genealogy community, and about guests family stories, and how genealogy impacted them.


You can contact me at thechosenfamiliesproject@gmail.com and find more about us here https://linktr.ee/thechosenfamiliesproject

title: My Mum Made Me (mom, relationships)
description:
An award-winning podcast on the relationships we have with our mums (or moms if you're not British).  Paul Reza Afshar explores the wonderful and sometimes weird ways our mums make us who we are today with famous faces from the BBC, The Witcher (Netflix) and ITV, opening up about the relationships with their mums. 


Over the course of a light-hearted 40-minute conversation, ‘My Mum Made Me’ explores the wonderful ways in which mums make successful actors, athletes, authors and activists, told through their childhood stories.

Behind every successful person is a magnificent mum, with all her love and eccentricities. And although we may not recognise them at the time, it’s these eccentricities that make us who are today.  My Mum Made Me unpacks the light and the dark when it comes to relationships with our mums.

title: Hiding in plain sight
description:
My truth, hidden in plain sight. 
I have been contemplating on what I should write, I am no longer searching the dark corners of my mind for material, mostly because it is right in front of me. 
People spend a lifetime hiding their most intimate secrets, ashamed or worried about what others may think of them; I do not have this luxury. 
The manifold that is my life includes so many once hidden treasures of emotional word candy. I use to believe (like most do) that I had to hide in the corner, face to the wall on my knees, arms bound with guilt and shame. 
I have been reluctant to start this new journey because my story impacts so many. Do I change names, do I alter the story, do I ask for permission? The first two are out of the question, the story would not be mine nor would it be true (as the title indicates).
I want to take a minute and describe the actors in my life, and I say actors as to me the relationship although real for the most part was fictitious.

title: Happily Ever Understood
description:
Imagine this world an even better place if we aim to understand its people's stories. Seeking to understand favors curiosity, patience, open-mindedness, and empathy. There is an absence of judgment and a desire to see things from others’ points of view, to see their reasons, and feel what they feel.

The more we seek understanding, the better we can craft our work. The better our work, the more likely we are to positively impact this world. Understanding is also a way to access knowledge, and knowledge is power. If you want to build a better place, start with listening. That is not all! Because if you listen well and try to understand all sides, you will find that you have so much more than your own story. Because in this world of ours that is so small and so fragile, we are bound together by stories. In such a world, curiosity, patience, open-mindedness, and empathy would be highly valued qualities. People would recognize the power of understanding and would actively strive to cultivate these qualities within themselves and their communities. By embracing the richness of diverse stories, this world would become a more harmonious and inclusive place, where every individual's experiences and perspectives are acknowledged and respected.

title: SadbutTrue Podcast
description:
SadbutTrue podcast is a refreshing take on the typical relationship podcast. Hosted by life long friends, Laurie and Crista. the podcast discusses personal relationships, including drama involving exes, current relationships, and friendships. The hosts also share their "Sad but True thoughts of the day," which range from humorous to thought-provoking.

One of the standout features of SadbutTrue podcast is its comical and quirky approach to discussing serious topics. The hosts are not afraid to laugh at themselves and their experiences, which makes the podcast relatable and enjoyable to listen to. They share their personal stories with honesty and vulnerability, which helps to create a sense of connection with their listeners.

Another strength of the SadbutTrue podcast is the knowledge and insight the hosts bring to the table. They are not afraid to delve into complex topics and offer their perspectives on them. Whether discussing the challenges of maintaining a long-distance relationship or the importance of setting boundaries in friendships, the hosts provide valuable advice and guidance for their listeners.

One of the most memorable aspects of the podcast is the "Sad but True thoughts of the day" segment. Each episode, the hosts share a thought-provoking quote or observation that encourages listeners to reflect on their own lives. The quotes are often humorous or witty, but they also offer genuine insight into the human experience.

Overall, SadbutTrue podcast is a must-listen for anyone interested in relationships, friendships, and personal growth. The hosts' comical and quirky approach to serious topics makes the podcast both entertaining and informative. Listeners will come away from each episode with a renewed sense of understanding and empathy for themselves and others 🤣 Its all SadbutTrue😘🤣🙌

title: Rare and Share Podcast
description:
Dobro došli na podcast!

Ovo je naše: “Zašto Rare & Share?”: 

Tokom lečenja sina od retke bolesti, a posebno nakon izlečenja imali smo prilike da upoznamo sjajne ljude i čujemo vrlo inspirativne priče. Ceo jedan svet sa svojim temama. 

Ovde ćemo pričati sa onima koji su pokretali lavine događaja, menjali okvire, pomerali granice do tada poznatog. Želimo da razgovaramo o temama koje su važne onima koji se suočavaju sa retkim izazovima kao što su pravni i zakonski okviri, aspekat psihološke podrške, medicinska dostignuća i nove studije. 

Planiramo razgovarati sa ekspertima, naučnicima, predstavnicima struke, razmenjivati argumente bazirane na činjenicama i zvaničnim podacima. Navedenim temama sa gostima, prilazićemo iz pozicija pacijenata, lekara, farmaceuta, države i svakog drugog ugla koji nam se učini važan.
Želimo da teme u vezi sa retkim bolestima približimo ćiroj publici. 

Znamo i kako.
Važno je deliti saznanja, informacije, iskustva.

title: Friend & Foe: The political divide is affecting our personal relationships
description:
Friend & Foe exists to give voice to the real conflict and distress people are feeling about the ways that the current political divide in the US is affecting personal relationships. For many, political alliances are a question of personal ethics and values, and what do you do when those that you have loved do not share your views? And what do you do when shared history or other ties are strong enough to want to try to maintain some connection despite these differences?

I believe listening is not the same as being complicit with ideas we don’t agree with.

If we sever all ties with those whose political beliefs we disagree with, how will be able to recognize the humanity in anyone who opposes our own beliefs?
As one of the people I interviewed stated, “If we can’t even talk to our family about this, how are we ever going to talk to strangers about it?”
This podcast is not about trying to make expert pronouncements on the subject, but rather an opportunity to give voice to the anxiety, sadness, and fear many are experiencing about this subject.

title: Two Weeks From Tuesday
description:
Two Weeks from Tuesday co-creators, Aliya Bloom and Erynn Wakefield have always connected through music. Most of their friendship has been long distance and paired with their busy lives, it seemed to be a recipe for disaster. But, over the years, they have shared music as a way to reach out, keep in touch, and keep tabs on each other. Whether it was through collaborative playlists, seasonal playlists, or even a quick song here and there; Two Weeks From Tuesday is unique in its approach, serving as a podcast as well as a platform for new artists. And when they can’t be live and talking to you, they’re still with you through corresponding playlists made for their listeners for every episode. 

This podcast truly wraps music and life into one entity and demonstrates how essential music is to the human experience. Most of all, Two Weeks From Tuesday aims to be honest. Co-creators, Aliya Bloom and Erynn Wakefield, truly want to reach out to their listeners with a helping hand and say, “we understand.”

title: The Highlife Uncut
description:
What is the High Life Uncut? 

The high Life Uncut is a podcast that discusses the lives of those that work in what is dubbed as Syd,Aus and/or Australia’s ‘Top Tier’ corporates. 


Who are the Podcast hosts Jen & Alex? 

Jen & Alex are Gen Z 9-5 corporates in a ‘Top Tier’ Australian bank. They are ambitious corporates who have combined 10-12 years experience across professional services, tourism, start-up, tech, fast moving consumer goods (fmcg) and financial services. 


Why The High Life Uncut? 

Jen & Alex realised there are conversations that we are afraid to strike up at times outside of the workplace or even with close friends. 

They talk through topics that can be uncomfortable to discuss from a male and female perspective. 

It’s about the fine art of balance between your personal life blurring into your career. 

Grab yourself a beveragino and find a spot to kick back so you can listen to The High Life Uncut.

title: Britt and Sax
description:
Link to Our Patreon - www.patreon.com/brittandsax to support us and you'll gain exclusive access to our special Weekend Edition episodes, dropping every Sunday night!

We are Britt and Saxon, a married couple in Denver with 2 kids, ages 5 and 6. We are both full time parents and independent working artists (rapper/comedian Old Man Saxon and filmmaker/musician Baby Luck).

Life is busy and messy, and we both do so much and feel so much the other person doesn't appreciate or even know about. So we decided to create this podcast, where we will each sit down separately for 3 minutes, 4 nights a week, Monday thru Thursday, to record what happened for us that day. We will not edit or do multiple takes. When our 3 minutes are up, we stop. Then it's the next person's turn. Simple!

On the weekends, we record our 30 minute Weekend Edition together, where we review the week and finish unfinished business, available exclusively on Patreon for as little as $5/month.

Making this podcast together is our way of doing something consistently and simply, in the midst of all our respective long term creative goals and projects, that often drain us and leave us feeling depleted. We hope you'll come along on this journey with us as we find our way by being candid, honest and most importantly, seeing and listening to each other. We'll do this as long as it helps our marriage.

Thank you for being here with us! We hope this makes you feel more connected in an increasingly disconnected world.

Love,

Britt and Sax

title: Mimosa Moments
description:
When life hands you lemons, throw them back and demand oranges! That’s
the premise of Jazz & Gina ‘s Mimosa Moment’s.

When purging with friends over brunch isn’t an option, buckle up for a ride
with Jazz & Gina for a little brunch therapy via “Mimosa Moments.

No topic is off limits with these two. Their candid conversations cover
everything from overcoming life’s challenges to sexual fantasies and even
menopause, yes, they cover that too. Each topic has a healthy dose of humor.
At times they feature various experts, celebrities, and comedians to forge
through discussions like mental health, finances, and self-doubt---all while
never losing their light-hearted touch and ability to laugh.

The frank and awkward discussions can be uncomfortable, but with their
humorous and good girlfriend delivery, listeners are reminded it’s exactly what
they needed. And that no matter how many lemons life gives you, or what you
have to overcome, a mimosa moment filled with giggles and girlfriends can be
the best dose of medicine a girl needs.

title: Humor, Grace & Grief with Debra Joy Hart RN and Jill Johnson-Young LCSW
description:
Join Jill Johnson-Young, LCSW (The Rebellious Widow) and Debra Joy Hart, RN, Grief Coach, as we speak into all things grief with a big helping of humor and grace. Message us and we will take up your ideas. 

Join us live on Fridays at the Humor, Grace and Grief facebook page: https://www.facebook.com/fridaygriefchat


Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/grieftalker
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/jilljohnson...
Twitter: https://twitter.com/jilljohnsonyou1
Websites: 
https://jilljohnsonyoung.com/
https://yourpaththroughgrief.com/

Jill Johnson-Young, LCSW is an author, international speaker, and clinician who specializes in death and dying and grief and loss. She co-owns a large private practice in Southern California, and teaches grief for therapists. She has written three children's books about grief, and an adult workbook. If and when COVID ever lifts she will be back on the road speaking at conferences about grief and dementia. In the meantime, she is online doing all the grief and dementia she can from home base.

Debra's links:
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/debra.j.hart.9
Website:  www.debrajoyhart.com 
Contact email: debrajoyhart@gmail.com

Debra Joy Hart, RN, BFA, CT, CLL-E, CHP, Joyologist has been a nurse for over 30 years and is currently a nurse consultant. Her nursing and teaching experience is in alcohol/drug rehabilitation, hospice, long term care, men’s emergency and transitional shelter, and public health. She’s the creator of the 1000 Red Nose Project NFP ™ and travels the world or sends her red noses to different countries, collecting pictures and handing out red noses to help promote peace, laughter and healthy humor in the world. Debra Joy is a Spiritual Director and part time minister at Unity Church and Spiritual Center in Urbana, IL. Since receiving her certification in thanatology (CT), she provides spiritual and grief support to members of the community.

title: Faith of the Centurion
description: It is hard to keep that faith, that motivation, that vigor that we had on Sunday going through the battles we must fight every day following. Join the discussion here with Dr. Stephen Woolverton, Associate Pastor at Chandler Light & Life Church, as we discover how to strengthen our faith together. We may charge into Monday with a sense of Godly purpose, but often our strength and determination tend to buckle under the weight of the world and daily stress. How can we deal with the pressures of work, school, family, relationships, society, and even self, when Sunday only comes once every seven days? In this podcast we discuss the battles you face during the week, and seek out biblical weapons we can use for our spiritual conflicts. I pray that you come away from these podcasts with a sense of hope, strength, and faith like that of the Centurion.

title: Inefable - Miryam & Jonathan

En este podcast hablamos de nuestra relación como pareja intercultural y de los miedos, expectativas, problemas, retos, pros y contras que conlleva, y de nuestra historia de amor compartida a través de la cual siempre encontramos una solución. 

Sobre nosotros:
Miryam(Miry) es de la Ciudad de México y vivió en México hasta 2019 antes de mudarse a Alemania. Estudió mercadotecnia en la Universidad Motolínea del Pedregal, maquillaje en la London Academy of Freelance Makeup y en el corto plazo "la danza como profesión" en Danceworks Berlín. Ahora trabaja como empleada en Berlín y busca nuevos retos.

Jonathan (Johnny) nació en Berlín y está a punto de terminar su licenciatura en guitarra de jazz en la Hochschule für Musik Dresden. Pronto le gustaría hacer un máster en composición o guitarra de jazz. Sus grandes pasiones, además de la música, son el club de fútbol 1.FC Union Berlin y el surf de olas. Trabaja de forma independiente como profesor de música y guitarra.

Ambos se conocieron en la preparatoria en Ciudad de México en 2011 cuando tenían 15 y 16 años respectivamente y han logrado mantener vivo su amor hasta hoy.

description: the art of growing up is a podcast all about stages of life, how to (and not to) chase your childhood dreams, taboo faith questions, disney cast member chats, college do's and don'ts, & how to romanticize every little era. hosted by Aly Brandal, the art of growing up is created to feel as though you're getting a voice memo from your best friend, relating to you & *attempting* to give you the best advice.

title: Collective Hearts Podcast
description: Collective Hearts was created by two lifelong friends, Harley and Tiffany, to share their life experiences and traumas in hopes of giving people a safe space to tell their own stories. We have found that talking about our hardships has helped us move forward in a lot of ways and that not everyone has someone they can confidently talk to about their own without judgement. We want to reach both women AND men and give everyone a place they feel heard!

title: As We Are
description:
The Women's Center podcast highlights the stories of those who exist in our community space around us, whose stories you may not know, but definitely should. From the serious to the not-so, our topics range from light-hearted hot-takes to discussions on important histories, happenings, and movements. Tune in to hear the lovely voices of your neighbors and @ us on Instagram to be featured on the show!
Cover Art By: Katie C. Lew

title: OUT
description: The OUT podcast provides a platform for LGBTQ+ people to tell their coming out stories. The series is meant to shine a light on the challenging and rewarding experience of claiming your identity, and celebrate a powerful unseen bond shared by those in the LGBTQ+ community. The podcast also aims to inspire and show solidarity to those in the community who are not yet able to come out. For some in the community, coming out is especially difficult. There may be safety issues, religious considerations, family pressures, or even a fear of death that prevents an individual from claiming their LGBTQ+ identity. Like the coming out experience itself, the format of the OUT podcast is meant to honor each individual's story. The interviewer allows each guest to freely tell their story without interruptions, and waits till their story is complete before engaging in a curious and genuine dialogue. Please enjoy the compelling stories of resilience, joy, and freedom in OUT.

title: Onto the Next
description: Stop dwelling, focusing on negativity, and putting energy into people and things that are no longer serving you.  Time is precious, so stay focused and keep moving forward; everything always turns out the way it is supposed to.  Molly is a 20-something, fun-loving, ambitious girl, who is trying to navigate through life and take advantage of new opportunities.  Join Molly as she talks about her thoughts, point of view, and how she is training her brain to make it happen and move onto the next.

title: Unscripted Faith
description:
Unscripted Faith is a Christian podcast for women, girls, wives, and mothers. We explore Biblical insights and offer Godly advice and instruction as we grapple with these confusing times we've found ourselves in. 
Our goal is to point listeners toward Jesus Christ, the Bible and help us grow in the knowledge and grace of God so we can become more effective teachers, disciples, and role models for the next generation. 
In this podcast, you will find clear, frank, candid, passionate, loving and sometimes humorous discussions on a variety of applicable topics that face women today. We cover a wide variety of topics from parenting teenagers, dating/courting/marriage, to homeschooling and theology to church matters, setting boundaries, worship, growing spiritually, mentoring and dealing with those ever elusive emotions that tend to muddy the waters for us as we live day by day in this crazy world.

title: Antioch Tulsa
description: A team of people planted Antioch Tulsa in the Summer of 2022. Challenging to build the culture less with the what Jesus did, and more with how Jesus related. Building a culture where Jesus is the cornerstone has been a challenge but these 6 relational values found in Jesus have helped us in building out Antioch Tulsa. Thanks for joining us! Hopeful Expectation Simple Honor Courageously Together Wholehearted Authenticity Submitted Communication Humble Responsibility

title: Nei šis, nei tas
description: Kuo gyvena ir apie ką kalbasi milenialsų poros? Kas joms neduoda ramybės ir kas yra taip svarbu? Šioje tinklalaidėje kartu bandom atsakyti į daugybę klausimų atvirai, šiltai ir be filtro. Tegyvuoja meilė ir įsimylėję žmonės!

title: Obstacles Under the Surface
description:
Finding and healing what navigates our life.
Unresolved patterns, experiences, and beliefs in our subconscious can impact our mindset and the decisions that we make in our life.  Working through any these challenges will put you at a better place, emotionally and psychologically.  Though we often address smaller and more detail-oriented issues, it is common to miss those that are under the surface and are subconscious.  Free yourself from this pull on your psyche and the negative impact on your life and relationships.  A life spent living is the greatest gift that we can give ourselves and our loved ones.

Our host Seth Melendez, a person of passion and an informed individual, this podcast offers a fresh perspective on the world around us. Each episode features in-depth discussions on a range of topics, from politics and current affairs to pop culture and entertainment. Whether you're looking to stay up-to-date on the latest happenings or just want to hear some engaging and thought-provoking conversation, "The Overnight Ramblings" has something for everyone. We have similar yet very different lifestyles and opinions! Deanna is a mother to 3 kids and a wife to Dina, to whom she has been married for 10 years. Jenn is an adoptive mother of one boy and newly married to her wife Chrissy.

description:
Heauxsome (ˈhō-suhm):

title: The Modern Independent Woman Winning at Love
description:
Hey strong beautiful independent woman. I know you must be tired of winning at most things in your life yet losing out at love. Here you will get the unfiltered truth about the mistakes you continue to make and how to solve them. No more endless searching in the wilderness for love. I've seen the ugly sides of dating and love and I've been lucky to enjoy some joyous moments as well. Over time I have realized a pattern that leads to failure and I learned these lessons the hard way. I am eager to share the knowledge gained over the years from my own experience and that of others who have also walked the path of pain and misery. You don't have to walk through the fire and get burned like I have and if you have a few scars of your own, let's work together to bring you to the other side unscathed. Its time to level up your dating game and get what you truly want in a love relationship. Say goodbye to suckers and settling for less because of the fear of being alone. You deserve the best and you can achieve it. Forgive my brashness but the truth will sometimes hurt. I will help you become the woman who gets what she wants from a man and more. Time to be a true boss lady in all areas of your life.

For free resources and community to help boss ladies win at love visit: https://bit.ly/helpingbossladieswinatlove

title: Hour of Healing
description: What do you need healing FROM, and what are you seeking healing TO. Everyone needs healing from something; physical, emotional, social, or spiritual burdens. All healing is from GOD. Each week, we will explore the right way to heal FROM wrong attitude TO the right attitude. A corrupt or bad soil cannot yield good fruit/food. This is the very bases for many disciplines advocating for more organic produce. When there is a disturbance in the bodies state of ease or comfort, don’t we end with dis-ease. Science teaches that all organ systems, including the skin function to maintain homeostasis. Imbalance leads to disorder which results in disease. The word dis-ease was first used to literally refer to lack of ease or comfort. The prefix ‘dis’ simply references the state of lack or disequilibrium. Thus, the simplest definition of healing is the process of putting at ease. Whether you are see a medical doctor, a psychiatrist, a spiritual healer or not, everyone needs healing. Subscribe, wherever you get your podcast. I can’t wait to see the lengths God takes us and what He chooses to do with these open conversations.

title: Hot & Heavy
description:
Welcome to Hot & Heavy where we get.... well... Hot & Heavy with our Topics!

Just two best friends chatting away about our hot takes on heavy subjects that affect the Gen Z population. From sex & dating to mental health to adulting to just life in general, we talk about it all and we are unapologetic to share our thoughts on how crazy this all can be. Our opinions are loud and proud and we aren't afraid to share it! Tune in every week for fun new content where we want to hear from you about the hot and heavy things in your life.

Our hosts are Donovan & Tiffany-Reece, past educators on topics regarding health & wellness for college-aged peers. They have spent the past couple of years learning about social trends and strategies for holistic wellness.

title: Chats With Cass | The O'Donnell Homestead
description: Here, we slow down. Here, we sit and chat about urban homesteading, homemaking, and slow living. We have the conversations that are difficult. We talk about life, we talk about our character, we talk about the people we hope and strive to be. We tell stories and listen with eager ears. Here, we turn back the clock a bit. Like sitting in front of the fire with your dearest loved ones. Taking the time to sip our coffee slow, and tuck into a conversation without the rush and propensity to move onto the next thing-fast and ferocious without any regard what we might be missing in the meantime. Let's learn to talk to one another again, and find the beauty in magic in conversation and storytelling. Let's Chat. Slainte!

title: PolyMoly!
description:
Hey daar! Wij zijn Louie (die/hij) en Manon (zij/haar), en we gaan al bijna drie jaar sterk als koppel. Maar we zijn niet zomaar een doorsnee paar – we zijn druk bezig met het verkennen van de wereld van ethische non-monogamie en polyamorie binnen onze relatie. En laten we eerlijk zijn, dat is soms best wel een kronkelige weg. We misten de ervaringen van anderen en inzichten tijdens dit avontuur, dus hebben we besloten om deze podcast te lanceren. "If you dont't see the change, be the change."

Ons doel? We willen graag onze frisse, nieuwe ervaringen met jou delen en hopen dat jij er ook iets uit kunt halen. Maar dat is niet alles. Naast het duiken in de wereld van ethische non-monogamie en polyamorie, snijden we ook regelmatig andere onderwerpen aan die gerelateerd zijn aan de LGBTQIAP+ gemeenschap.

Maar, en dit is belangrijk, we willen wel even duidelijk maken dat we niet de alleswetende experts zijn. In feite nemen we je mee in ons proces terwijl we zelf nog aan het ontdekken zijn. We weten dat we onderweg tegen allerlei uitdagingen gaan aanlopen. Dus, neem alsjeblieft niet alles wat we zeggen als dé onwrikbare waarheid, maar eerder als onze gedachten en bevindingen op dat moment.

Als je nog dieper in de onderwerpen wilt duiken die we bespreken, raden we je zeker aan om naast onze podcast ook andere bronnen te raadplegen. Hoe dan ook, we hopen dat je ontzettend veel plezier beleeft aan het luisteren naar onze gesprekken!

Oh, en vergeet niet om ons te volgen:

https://instagram.com/polymolydepodcast?igshid=MzNlNGNkZWQ4Mg==

Bopha & Sully will take you on a journey to where they came from and what they’ve learned along the way from relationships, parenting, entrepreneurship, self-development and so much more!

Bopha & Sully wants to inspire relationship building through the diverse art of storytelling.  They look forward to having a collective group of storytellers with different lenses to join in on their conversation.

Please join Bopha & Sully as they make their debut in the podcast industry on January 25, 2023.

The Garden of Storytelling, a welcoming and safe space where the seed of communication is planted for the mind, body and soul to evolve, change and grow.

title: Intimate Inspirations
description:
Welcome to the Intimate Inspirations podcast. A Podcast inspired by my desire to help women see themselves as the princess God created them to be. I believe that all women have the desire to be beautiful, both inside and out. Unfortunately, we also have insecurities, whether big or small, that often keep us from finding our beautiful. Most often, these insecurities are simply the lies about ourselves that we believe, or have been told, rather than believing who and whose we are. In this podcast, I will be encouraging women, no matter what season of life they are walking through, that even though life is crazy, busy, and often tangled, they are not alone. I will be providing gentle reminders and ways to be a better "you", not only for yourself, but for those who you do everyday life with! I will also be diving into topics on intimacy in marriage and ways to spice things up a little!

I am Michele Blumentritt, and I am your host. I am looking forward to walking through life's journey with you and sharing my experiences that have brought me to this point. I am the youngest of three girls. I have been married for 24 years to man who loves the Lord and leads our family with strength and dedication. I have 3 beautiful children, a son and two beautiful daughters. My passion and excitement to share with other women how to find their beautiful are what inspired this podcast. Life is full of twists and turns, let's navigate through them together!

title: RICH RELATIONSHIPS REFUGE
description: Rich Relationships Refuge podcast with Gilbert J and Renée M. Beavers is fantastic because it's the best place to really explore the reality of relationships — the good, the bad, and the painful and confusing. This podcast helps to illuminate what it means to be intimate with others and what it teaches people about them. It will make you want to strive for a kinder, more fun relationship with others. Many individuals don't have room in their hearts or life for people due to unforgiveness, regret, shame, and uncommunicated expectations. Rich Relationships is an experience with principles to learn. There are tools to use with an emphasis on building, repairing, and restoring relationships with individuals and families in a safe community environment that will stand in a world that's falling apart. Gil and Renée are originally from Detroit, Michigan. Their relationship started with Renée rolling the pencil off her desk and Gil picking it up. They never knew such a small act would create a 37-year legacy of love. Gil and Renée were only 21 when they happily committed to until death do us part. Gil retired from the Air Force, and Renée is a former salon owner who has been an entrepreneur and now an author for over 30 years. They have lived in over 13 cities throughout the United States and Germany. They are proud parents to an amazing and talented daughter, Aharon (pronounced like Sharon, except with an A). After a family tragedy, they also adopted Renée's little sisters (Carmen and Monique).This couple has helped many other couples establish a new habit of love to strengthen their marriage relationship through their tested relationship tools and principles and as marriage facilitators through the Prepare and Enrich Marriage program. Rich Relationship with Gil & Renèe podcast is back and ready to move forward and deeper into our relationship strengths and growth areas. Let's get empty of the pain from our past, unforgiveness, resentment, shame, and uncommunicated expectations.Our mission is to empower singles and couples to experience greater intimacy and fulfillment in their relationship with God, themselves, food, and money. This year our podcast will feature individuals and small business owners regarding their impact in these four areas. Gil and Renèe are looking forward to serving you and your relationships. Remember, you are more than enough! Now let's learn to live like it together!. YOU ARE MORE THAN ENOUGH! https://makingheadlinenews.com/2020/09/05/new-book-alert-alabama-couple-gil-and-renee-m-beavers-newly-produced-anthology-figures-to-have-a-massive-kingdom-impact/?fbclid=IwAR1dO2EfUCg3p1KZuCOu5dM5YsNYPJ84FKxA06o7W9HyVHUtaBJoJ1tsZRA https://youtu.be/Z8QoFNV1xg4

title: The Conquered Mind Podcast
description:
The Conquered Mind Podcast is designed for anyone who is striving to create the best versions of themselves through conquering their mindsets. This podcast will serve as a basis for anyone needing direction, purpose, or 'wake-up call' in creating the mindset needed to achieve their personal levels of success. 

In this podcast, we use a mixture of research (neurology, psychology, cognitive) and personal experiences (substance abuse, mental health, trauma) to more effectively understand how the body and brain function together. Through having a deeper understanding of these correlations along with increased self-awareness, it makes it easier to evolve your mindset to succeed in this world.

Through listening to our podcast, you will begin to come to the realization that YOU control your life. That means if you actually want to upgrade your mindset, find success or whatever you want out of this life, YOU have to make it happen

Once you can conquer your mind, then you can conquer life. 

The good news is, we will provide you with all the tools and guidance to allow for this growth to happen through our podcast. If you are ready to conquer your mindset, take that next step in life or just looking for extra motivation, then please tune into The Conquered Mind Podcast!

Presented by: @unstoppablemind__

En HELEL, nos apasiona ofrecer servicios de consultoría de gestión de alta calidad y adaptados a los objetivos que añadan valor y ayuden a nuestros clientes a alcanzar el éxito. Nuestro equipo de expertos cuenta con una amplia experiencia en transformación digital, consultoría de negocio, consultoría estratégica y desarrollo empresarial, y aportamos una gran cantidad de conocimientos y experiencia a cada proyecto que emprendemos.

Nuestro enfoque en la excelencia profesional y el compromiso de ofrecer resultados de alta calidad nos diferencia de otras empresas de consultoría. Nuestro objetivo es construir relaciones duraderas con nuestros clientes, y estamos muy orgullosos de los resultados que conseguimos para ellos.

title: GLOW2IT
description:
GLOW2IT is a podcast that dives into the many realms of professional development, communication, relationships, motivational speakers, comedians, and public figures, all to ensure that we shine our brightest and glow. It’s a pun that I thought was funny while driving; growing up – Shine Bright Like a Diamond – Brighter – Sun – Bright Learner – Glow Up – Lead Up – Lead to it – Glow2it! Phew, I finally got there! See a little comedy as well!

So, with that, we’re creating a podcast that enables the knowledge you seek to glow in your way and shares the benefits that help grow your mindset and how you communicate and develop the skills so you can burn to your brightest potential. 

Our goal is to cultivate a space of collective knowledge of professional development, mindfulness, resiliency, and communication skills that build you to be the brightest you can be!

Growing up, my parents always said, “… you have to grow up…” so that’s what I’m doing alongside some of my favorite professional development writers, public speakers, motivational storytellers, and many more because I know that I can’t shine my brightest if I haven’t grown up, if I haven’t Glow2it!

title: Als zwanger worden niet zo natuurlijk is.
description:
In deze podcast serie delen wij, Lis en Ruben, ons verhaal. Wij zijn al 5 jaar bezig om natuurlijk zwanger te worden. Dit heeft helaas nog niet mogen gebeuren.

Wij zijn geen artsen of deskundigen, maar gewoon een stel bij wie dit proces niet vanzelf gaat en ons verhaal willen delen. ​

Er gebeurt van alles om ons heen. Artsen die zeggen dat er niets aan de hand is en bij de volgende arts sta je al ingepland voor IVF en moet de baarmoeder per direct in een kunstmatige menopauze gebracht worden.

Dan zijn er nog vrienden die niet zwanger willen worden en het ineens zijn (oepsie), stellen die moeite hebben om ons te vertellen dat ze zwanger zijn en onze omgeving die het ons zo graag gunt dat ze overal van op de hoogte gehouden willen worden. ​

Maar wat willen wij nou echt? Gaan we mee met de maatschappelijke norm of willen we echt graag kinderen. Iedereen heeft een mening hierover en die kan soms je eigen zicht vertroebelen.

​In deze podcast luister je naar ons verhaal, onze twijfels, onze pijn en ook ons geluk. We nemen je als luisteraar mee in het proces wat we al gehad hebben en wat nog voor ons ligt.

Veel luisterplezier

Liefs Lis en Ruben

Kijk ook op: https://www.zwangerwordennietzonatuurlijk.nl/
