title: One Brain at a Time
description:
Have you ever wondered what your therapist is thinking? Join Dr. K and Dr. J as they share educational, professional, and personal experiences on the topic of brain wellness. Being licensed therapists, these sisters bring a unique perspective to the conversation of destigmatizing mental health through a holistic lens. If you want to learn about effective communication, family dynamics, diagnoses, therapy, and so much more, this podcast is for you!

Dr. Kristen Davies PhD, LMHC has over 20 years of professional mental health experience. Her passion has remained focused on destigmatizing mental health and educating her clients, staff, and colleagues on the importance of brain wellness. Dr. K has experience working in numerous areas of mental health including inpatient settings, private practice (couples therapy), and child/family crisis work. She’s always prepared to help individuals navigate their mental health journey no matter what stage of the process they’re in. Outside of work, Dr. K is a certified yoga instructor and is obsessed with anything dark chocolate.

Dr. Jody McGrath PhD, LMHC has worked in the mental health field for nearly 20 years and has a PhD in Health Psychology. Her work has primarily focused on trauma with a specialty in anxiety/panic/OCD, through the lens of how brain health impacts our behavior. Over the years, Dr. J has provided comprehensive clinical care to military, law enforcement, and first responders. She has also worked extensively in addiction, hospice care, and residential education. Dr. J has a passion for building a safe and secure environment for all her clients. When she isn’t working, she loves to travel, spend time with her family, and find the perfect cup of coffee.

title: Convertidos POD
description:
Bem-vindo ao nosso podcast CONVERTIDOS POD, onde todas as segundas e sextas-feiras às 11 horas da manhã, compartilhamos uma palavra para ajudá-lo a se conectar com Deus.

Neste podcast, Raphael e Hermes, Hosts do Convertidos POD compartilham suas perspectivas sobre a Palavra de Deus e como aplicá-la em sua vida diária. Nós nos esforçamos para trazer uma mensagem edificante e encorajadora a cada episódio, com a esperança de que você possa se sentir mais conectado com Deus e sua fé fortalecida.

Se você está procurando inspiração e orientação espiritual, este podcast é para você. Acreditamos que a Palavra de Deus é uma fonte de sabedoria e conforto, e estamos dedicados a ajudá-lo a crescer em sua fé e encontrar significado em sua jornada cristã.

Então, junte-se a nós todas as segundas e sextas-feiras às 11 horas da manhã, e deixe-nos ser uma parte do seu dia, enquanto nos conectamos juntos com Deus.

title: Las Krtas sobre la mesa
description:
¿Qué pasa en el mundo que avanza tan rápido? Los cambios sociales han sido contundentes, las relaciones humanas, estilos de vida, tendencias y la manera de relacionarnos. En un entorno donde las brechas de idiología y generacionales nos han planteado muchas dudas, incertidumbre e incomodidades. Pero tambien un cambio en las libertades y la forma en la queramos vivir nuestra vida.

En este podcast investigaremos, debatiremos y confrontaremos de la mano de nuestros invitados esos temas que mas nos incomodan pero al mismo tiempo mas nos interesan. Sin tabús ni condiciones: Las cartas sobre la mesa.

title: Don't Say We Didn't Warn You

Don’t Say We Didn’t Warn You… this isn’t your average podcast!

Join Ashley and Rebecca weekly as they give you completely unfiltered advice and warnings about all things motherhood, teaching, friendship, anxiety, marriage, and more. This thing called life isn’t easy, and sometimes you just need some besties that aren’t afraid to tell you the honest truth about how it REALLY is.

So, grab your Stanley and your snacks and get ready to talk about the things nobody talks about… all while laughing and feeling reassured.

So did the extensive travel he did during his career. And finally, there's just life itself. Not that Paul's life is any more interesting than anyone else's. But his perspective is.

description: We are just two friends who sit and talk honestly with each other. We talk about love, life, kids and even mental health... or lack thereof. We believe humor heals all wounds. Don't let our light hearted banter confuse you though. We talk about some hard topics. We will touch on a variety of things. It's a show about nothing and everything all at the same time. title: Understanding Microchurch: Recapturing the Power of Close Community
description:
The normal expression of a Christian church is small.

In the United States, most congregations number fewer than 80 people. Across the world, the numbers are even smaller.

Big churches are the anomalies. However, large congregations that effectively operate as clusters of small ones are a growing phenomenon. We'll explore how this model is poised to plant new congregations outside the circle if their own fellowships.

Recapturing the power of "small" is key to fulfilling the Acts 1:8 imperative to take the gospel from our local communities to people nearby but somewhat unlike us and then to the far corners of the earth.

Das erste Jahr mit Baby neigt sich dem Ende zu und in den letzten Monaten habe ich viele tolle Ratschläge von Hohlfritten und Besserwissern bekommen, habe versucht im Chaos als Neu-Mama und trotz Schlafmangel eine "gute Mutter" zu sein. Am Ende des Tages versuche ich es trotzdem irgendwie mit Humor zu nehmen.

In diesem Podcast erzähle ich von meinen Erfahrungen, teile meine Geschichten mit euch und lade den ein oder anderen Experten zu einem Kaffeeklatsch über wichtige Themen der Mama-Welt ein.

title: Royally Confident
description:
Welcome to "Royally Confident," your safe haven for reclaiming your self-worth and embracing a life filled with confidence and love after surviving the storm of a toxic relationship. I'm Genese, your compassionate host, and this podcast is dedicated to your healing journey.

We understand that escaping a toxic relationship can leave deep emotional scars. Our mission is to provide a supportive, empathetic community where you can find solace, inspiration, and expert guidance on your path to renewal.

What You'll Discover on "Royally Confident":

- Empathetic Stories: Listen to real-life stories of resilience and recovery from me & other survivors who have emerged stronger after toxic relationships. You're not alone in this journey.

- Healing and Self-Care: Explore effective self-care strategies and healing techniques that foster emotional well-being. Your healing is a priority, and we're here to guide you.

- Dating with Confidence: We offer practical advice on navigating the dating scene post-toxic relationship. Learn to recognize red flags and make choices that align with your newfound confidence.

- Community and Support: Join our empathetic community, where you can share your experiences, ask questions, and find understanding voices that uplift and empower you.

Remember, your past does not define your future. You are deserving of healthy, loving relationships, and we are here to help you rediscover your inner strength and self-assuredness.

Subscribe to "Royally Confident" today to embark on a transformative journey toward self-love, confidence, and authenticity. Together, we will rise above the challenges and emerge royally confident.

Connect with us on social media and our website to be a part of our growing community. Your voice matters, and your story deserves to be heard.

title: What If I Soar Podcast
description:
Welcome to "But What If I Soar" Podcast! Join us on an empowering journey of self-discovery and healing as we navigate the intricate world of mental health. In this transformative podcast, we bring together the unique perspectives of a seasoned BIPOC licensed social worker, resilience, self-advocacy, and transformation life coach, and a BIPOC licensed professional counselor with over 15+ years of experience in the field.

Through thought-provoking discussions and heartfelt personal anecdotes, we explore a wide range of topics, from coping skills and self-care techniques to the profound impact of current events on our mental well-being, with a particular focus on minority communities. Our aim is to shed light on the challenges we all face and provide invaluable guidance for navigating life's inevitable ups and downs. Along the way, we will share our own real-life experiences of overcoming obstacles, finding healing, and cultivating gratitude.

In each episode of "But What If I Soar," we dive deep into the complexities of mental health. We explore the nuances of various mental health conditions, challenge stigmas associated with seeking help, and discuss strategies for building resilience and fostering positive mental well-being.

Our podcast is not just about information—it's about transformation. We believe in the power of storytelling and vulnerability, and we share our personal journeys to inspire and connect with our listeners. By hearing our stories and those of our guests, you'll realize that you're not alone in your struggles. We aim to create a safe space where you can find solace, inspiration, and actionable steps to embark on your own path of healing and personal growth.

"But What If I Soar" is more than just a podcast; it's a community. We invite you to join us in this collective journey toward self-discovery and healing. Through engaging conversations and interactive segments, we encourage you to share your thoughts, ask questions, and contribute to the discussion. Your voice matters, and we want to create an inclusive space where everyone feels heard and supported.

Whether you're seeking guidance, inspiration, or simply a sense of connection, our podcast is here for you. Tune in to "But What If I Soar" and let's soar to new heights, one episode at a time. Together, we'll unravel the complexities of mental health, discover inner strength, and embrace the transformative power of healing. Get ready to embark on a journey of self-discovery and empowerment like never before.

Subscribe to our podcast on your favorite platforms like Spotify, Apple Podcasts, or Google Podcasts, and be sure to follow us on Instagram, Facebook, and Twitter for updates, sneak peeks, and behind-the-scenes content. We can't wait to have you join our community and embark on this transformative journey together. Remember, you have the power to soar—let's do it together!
author_name: But What If I Soar Podcast

title: El nefelibata somnoliente

Contiene episodios personales sobre mis pensamientos y mis elucubraciones sobre temas varios de la sociedad, del arte, del sexo y de la vida en general.

Un nefelibata es un individuo desconectado de la realidad práctica, es una mente fantasiosa que aspira a introducir el encanto en su vida y en la de la gente que se aproxima a su persona.

El formato de los episodios es como el de un cuento para espíritus adultos, enriquecidos por un hilo musical suave y en armonía con los textos.

Preferentemente a escuchar por las noches antes de dormir o en momentos diurnos de serenidad y sosiego.

En cualquier caso, a escuchar cuando la mente está en estado de somnolencia y de vagancia, sea a la luz del sol, sea a la luz de la luna.

title: Soul Speak with Meg Michaelson
description:
I am Meg Michaelson. Founder of SoulSpeak Integrative Healing and Well House 1900. Almost 30 years ago, I awoke to a realization that changed my life.

We are humans, in a very messy world, and too often we forget the incredibleness that our soul is urging us to remember. Our soul that is always trying to communicate with us to live in the beautiful ways we came here to live. To push us to be awake, even when and especially when, we are too tired to do so.

I have a mission in this lifetime, to help people live in the truth, to help us live in the balance. To help us live knowing we can find love every day, learning to live in the balance of our inner feminine and masculine. I have a mission to help others take more risks, and step away from the fear and into the unknown. Not alone, but with the connection of our souls.

During our weekly time together, we will share stories of moments from all aspects of our lives, and we will meet other humans trying to live a life awake too. We will learn how to connect our earth life to the language of our soul life, and invite this connection into every earthly experience.

title: SuperMom University! The Podcast With Shauna D. Harrison

Through my years of experience and God-given wisdom, SuperMom University wants nothing but your commitment to show up and BECOME all that you were created to become. 21st Century motherhood is DIFFERENT. I'm a wife, mother, Pastor & Prophetic voice for this generation, a mental health coach, entrepreneur, and author and SU is about to change your life for the better. Join me on this journey and let's raise Godly, relentless kids, nieces, and nephews and give them the kind of mothers, aunties, and grandmothers that every kid deserves. You're already a Boss, now It's time to continue to BECOME!

title: Stories For Ahmed
description:
Welcome to "Stories for Ahmed," by Dr. Lacey, a podcast born from a deep friendship, countless adventures, and an unyielding passion for storytelling. This show peels back the layers of Dr. Lacey's colourful life, chronicling the laughter, tears, triumphs, and trials that have shaped her journey.

Dr. Lacey, a natural storyteller and entertainer, opens her vast trove of life experiences to captivate you with tales from different eras of her life. Each episode, carefully curated and woven into an audio tapestry, promises to take you on a wild ride through unexpected turns, teaching lessons, evoking emotions, and most importantly, celebrating life.

One of the most ardent fans of Dr. Lacey's stories is her dear friend, Ahmed. His fascination and intrigue with her tales inspired the birth of this podcast. Every story told here has been a part of their shared memories, whispered secrets in hushed tones, or loud laughter echoing in rooms. And now, these stories are brought to life for all to enjoy. Whether you're a friend, family, or a curious listener, each episode offers a window into the extraordinary life of Dr. Lacey.

Expect heartwarming anecdotes, hilarious misadventures, stories of love and loss, and the wisdom that comes from a lifetime of learning. From her childhood escapades to her scholarly pursuits, her travels around the globe to the quiet moments of introspection, there's a story for everyone here. This podcast, above all, cherishes human connection and the magic of shared stories.

While "Stories for Ahmed" is indeed a tribute to a beautiful friendship, it's also an invitation for every listener to step into the shoes of Dr. Lacey and experience the world from her perspective. Join us in this intimate exploration of life's many wonders and oddities, and be ready to see the world anew.

So grab a cup of coffee, find a comfortable spot, and let Dr. Lacey's enchanting voice take you on a journey like no other. Welcome to "Stories for Ahmed, by Dr. Lacey". Let the adventure begin!

title: Casual Fridays Podcast by I Read Aloud
description:
The Casual Fridays podcast is where personal experiences, anecdotes and storytelling are used to explore weekly themes. I hope to infect my audience with a positive outlook on life, no matter how dark the topic.

This podcast was borne from my channel, I Read Aloud, where I mainly post poetry and short story readings.

After about 9 months of such posts, I began posting more personal content on Fridays on both Instagram and TikTok. After a while I realized that I would like to say more than the time allowed on these two apps, and that was how this podcast came to life.

I hope you enjoy my take on things and I also hope you will engage with me in the comments section. Nothing brings me more pleasure than interacting with my listeners.

Don't forget to subscribe to my YouTube channel, and to check out my content on Instagram and TikTok, on @ireadaloud.

Your passionate reader and podcast host,

Dada

title: The Truth About Us
description:
We live in this world according to who we believe we are, or whatever abilities we believe we possess. Whether we regard ourselves as helpless people who are ill equipped to deal with the challenges of life, or people who are fully able and confident enough to live up to the purpose of life, it all depends on who we think we are.

Every week, Goitsemang reveals the connection between the mind and the body in a relationship we regard as being human. He explains how they both work together, with the mind in charge, to create the things we experience every day. All this to emphasize our oneness with each other as people, and with the things we create.

My official website: oneppp.xyz - please check for all the other services I offer.

My book: “We Are God – The Power is Within Us” can be found on Amazon.com, in both paperback and kindle.

title: With You
description:
"With You" là một chương trình tâm sự và thấu hiểu độc giả, nơi bạn có thể chia sẻ những câu chuyện của mình về cuộc sống, tình yêu, công việc, gia đình, bạn bè và những vấn đề cá nhân khác. Chúng tôi sẽ lắng nghe và hỗ trợ bạn, đồng thời cung cấp lời khuyên và thông tin có thể giúp bạn giải quyết các vấn đề của mình.

Chúng tôi tin rằng tất cả mọi người đều có những câu chuyện đáng được chia sẻ và lắng nghe. Chúng tôi muốn tạo ra một nơi an toàn và thân thiện, nơi bạn có thể chia sẻ những suy nghĩ và cảm xúc của mình mà không phải lo lắng về việc bị phán xét.

Nếu bạn đang tìm kiếm một nơi để chia sẻ câu chuyện của mình, thì hãy liên hệ với chúng tôi ngay hôm nay. Chúng tôi luôn sẵn sàng lắng nghe và hỗ trợ bạn.

title: For the "U" in ME!!
description:
Its really crazy to find an answer for the question " Who are you"?. I really wonder where can or when can I find that answer. Is it the 8yr old saying out loud to her teacher that I want to be a doctor or an 8yr old told by her mom that be a good human which is the basic step to the above asked questions.

So this podcast is exactly about the then 8yr old girl who turned to a 24yr lady and still stammering Infront of this question.

title: Pond.ering
description: Hi, we are Nick & Kat :) We have been thrown our fair share of curveballs during our 5 years together. All of these experiences forced us to deconstruct and rebuild our beliefs over and over, and what we've learned through these experiences is that we don't know much at all. We live in a state of constant Pond.ering. We are always questioning and wondering "why?" We are trying to find new perspectives and experiences to help us understand this life of ours, but we don't think we'll ever find the answers and that's okay. We are good with the Pond.ering. Come hang out with us every week while we Pond.er into the mic about the big and small life questions, discuss interesting topics & hear stories of others who are in a state of Pond.ering as well. Let's all try to figure this life out together, or at least build a community of people who are good with being in the Pond.ering state of life.

title: The Heartbreak Happy Hour
description:
Welcome to "The Heartbreak Happy Hour," the podcast where it's just you and me as we dive into fascinating topics, personal stories, and thought-provoking conversations. I'm your host Da Heartbreak Kid.

Today, we have a soul-stirring episode in store for you. As always, we'll start with a brief introduction to the topic and then dive deeper. So, grab your favorite drink, get cozy, and let's begin!

In today's episode, we're going to explore the topic of marriage and divorce. But first, let me share a personal story related to this topic.

Personally, I've experienced one and I'm currently experiencing the other. At one point I'd found the person I wanted to spend the rest of my life with, but it didn't go as planned. We'd been married for awhile, but I did stuff to cause us to separate. Although we're not divorced, we're still friends, but I still wanna spend my life with her. Being separated completely shifted my perspective on what true love is.

Now that we've explored my personal experience, let's dive deeper into the topic itself. This podcast isn't just about me talking. I want to hear from you. If you have any stories, questions or thoughts related to today's topic, you can email me at Da_Heartbreak_Kid@mail.com using #The Heartbreak Happy Hour. I'll answer your queries in future episodes.

As we near the end of today's episode, I want to leave you with some final thoughts. Remember, if you find a good man or woman you need to hold on to them, the grass is NEVER greener on the other side.

Thank you for joining me on this episode of "The Heartbreak Happy Hour." If you enjoyed it, don't forget to subscribe and leave a review on your favorite podcast platform. Tune in next week as we explore another captivating topic. Until then, keep taking care of yourselves and loving one another!

title: Trueness Of The Words with Elenor A. Fleming
description:
Trueness Of The Words Is a Place For Women Where We Are Authentic & Vulnerable!

ABOUT ELENOR:

For Women Authentic & Vulnerable we are! Trueness Of The Words was birthed in me over a decade ago. I could not understand it then why the name came to me so clearly or how I would ever be able to actually use it. What I was clear on, was that God had given me the name.

I have a strong desire within to give an Authentic and Vulnerable voice to the issues that come upon women, mother & daughter relationships, single women and married women by way of my own hurts and pains that I carry daily and some the daily has turned into years. Longsuffering is what the Word of God calls it. The voice I will give will come with truth, hurts, pains, vulnerability, beginnings, endings, unforgiveness that God has brought me through over to forgiveness and some that I’m still struggling with. Trusting the Lord through it all can be done, but the Authentic and Vulnerable voice understands even as a follower of Jesus Christ it’s not always easy as we are often told. Study: Gal 5:22; 6:7 and Cor 3:6-9

Subscribe to this podcast and Join me as we take this journey together, as two are better than one (Ecclesiastes 4:9-12). I will be Authentic and Vulnerable as I will share my experiences, along with guests that I’m taking time to ask God in prayer for His guidance alone, for who they are to be, so that we can help you achieve a peace and relation with our Father in heaven that cannot be moved by the things and obstacles on our earthly path.

We champion a bilateral dialogue in the spirit of collaborative entrepreneurship, valuing intellectual and moral integrity in all our initiatives. Our operations are shaped by a unique organizational culture rooted in stakeholder theory, emphasizing that an institution must be answerable to all components of society, not just a select few.

At the China-US Salon, we firmly believe that progress and mutual understanding are fostered by bringing together individuals from diverse backgrounds who possess the determination and influence to instigate positive change.

title: The Kitchen Table | Queer Conversations
description:
Welcome to "The Kitchen Table; Queer Conversations," where the warmth of heartfelt discussions meets the power of vulnerability. Join couple Jasper (they/them) and Rae (she/her) as we pull up a chair and create a safe, inviting space for candid, fearless and sometimes spicy conversations about all things queer.

Around our metaphorical kitchen table, we explore the diverse tapestry of queer stories, identities, and experiences. From love, sex and relationships to spirituality, self-discovery, and everything in between, our podcast is a place where challenges become catalysts for growth and where laughter and love reign supreme.

Each episode invites you to join us in stirring the pot, setting the table for dialogue that matters, and embracing authenticity. Our guests share their unique journeys, revealing the beauty, resilience, and transformation that can emerge from the power of storytelling.

Whether you identify as LGBTQ+ or as an ally, "The Kitchen Table; Queer Conversations" is a space for everyone to learn, connect, and find inspiration in the shared experiences of our diverse community. Join us as we explore the ever-evolving landscape of queerness, one heartfelt conversation at a time.

Subscribe, pull up a chair, and let's embark on this journey together. Because around our kitchen table, everyone's story is welcome, and every voice matters.

title: Welcome to Conversations at Midnight | A Podcast for Black Women
description:
Hey ya'll! I'm just a regular around-the-way girl who had an idea, a purpose, and saw a need for a podcast such as this to be created.

Conversations at Midnight is a podcast created and designed by a black woman for black women. Black women are becoming entrepreneurs, trailblazers, and trendsetters. On the road toward academia and career success, there are many barriers that black women face in efforts to get society’s standard of “making it.”

Conversations at Midnight is a place for vulnerable and honest conversations to take place between black women to share issues that we all may be going through (or struggling through) in private.

There will be guest appearances by real, normal, and relatable women with impactful testimonies that have the power to change, heal, and restore the older generations and the next.

Subscribe to Conversations at Midnight on YouTube, Spotify, and Google Podcasts. I promise it’s a conversation that you DON’T want to miss!

title: The Black Lives Chatter Podcast
description: Introducing The Black Lives Chatter Podcast: a transformative podcast that dives deep into the heart of what it means to be Black in today's ever-changing world. Our goal is to take an engaging & thoughtful approach to exploring the nuances of Black culture, & foster candid conversations designed to define & refine our collective experience. Our hosts, who are fervent advocates for the empowerment & growth of the Black community, lead the charge by addressing a wide spectrum of topics, from relationships & marriage to the social, economic, & political issues that impact our lives. Their mission is to provide a platform for a myriad of voices, ensuring that every perspective is heard & valued. They also seek to challenge existing narratives, delve into the unique experiences of their guests, & strive to foster understanding & unity. By embracing our shared stories & engaging in open, honest dialogue, we can redefine the contours of Black culture, & shape a brighter future. Subscribe now and let's embark on this journey together!

These figures have freely poured in their time, wisdom, and resources, and have shaped who I am today. This podcast is to highlight & share those relationships and I hope that it would beneficial for you as well!

Believers who wish to strengthen their faith, entertainment, and fellowship. But ultimately it’s for the glory of God. So join us as we discuss all things faith, walking with Jesus, friendship, and discipleship.

title: Lessons from Love Addiction
description: Listen to learn all about the lessons i've gleaned from battling Love Addiction. Also, what causes Love Addiction, and how to recover. We're in this together! Solution-oriented with a spiritual slant, this podcast is a reminder that we don't need to search externally for love, because the love we've been seeking has been inside of us all along. 💗
